        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 10:43PM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 1043 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles west of Mud Buttes, or 21 miles southeast of Baker, moving
northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rhame, Marmarth, Mud Buttes, Griffin, and Sunset Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
